{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019bcuuA9XLnyC7fC8ohR2hM","type":"tool_result","content":"Proof document written. Here's the summary:\n\n**4 of 7 ACs pass. Overall: FAIL.**\n\n| AC | Result | Detail |\n|----|--------|--------|\n| 1 | **FAIL** | Patch file lacks \"### Observability Evidence\" section |\n| 2 | **FAIL** | \"Step 3.5\" doesn't exist anywhere in v0.23.1 package |\n| 3 | **PASS** | `parseObservabilityGaps` correctly returns `{totalACs:8, gapCount:2, coveredCount:6}` = 75% |\n| 4 | **PASS** | `verifyStory()` populates both `observabilityGapCount` and `runtimeCoveragePercent` |\n| 5 | **PASS** | `saveRuntimeCoverage()` persists to `observability.runtime` in sprint-state.json |\n| 6 | **PASS** | Returns `skipped: true` with warning when backend unreachable, does NOT fail |\n| 7 | **FAIL** | Patch doesn't instruct verifiers to include observability evidence |\n\nThe core issue: the v0.23.1 npm package installed in the container does not include Story 5.2's changes (patch file update, verify prompt template with Step 3.5). The runtime infrastructure (gap parser, coverage persistence, graceful degradation) all work correctly — they were implemented in earlier epics.\n\n**Bonus finding**: `readPatchFile()` has a path resolution bug — it resolves `../../patches/` from `dist/` which goes outside the package directory. Patch files are never loaded from disk; the hardcoded fallback templates are always used.\nShell cwd was reset to /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e4658086-9562-443f-b0a9-42e8d393ffab","uuid":"df632bf5-7ae1-4b95-b178-4e27d53d6ef6","timestamp":"2026-03-21T06:53:08.657Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"Proof document written. Here's the summary:\n\n**4 of 7 ACs pass. Overall: FAIL.**\n\n| AC | Result | Detail |\n|----|--------|--------|\n| 1 | **FAIL** | Patch file lacks \"### Observability Evidence\" section |\n| 2 | **FAIL** | \"Step 3.5\" doesn't exist anywhere in v0.23.1 package |\n| 3 | **PASS** | `parseObservabilityGaps` correctly returns `{totalACs:8, gapCount:2, coveredCount:6}` = 75% |\n| 4 | **PASS** | `verifyStory()` populates both `observabilityGapCount` and `runtimeCoveragePercent` |\n| 5 | **PASS** | `saveRuntimeCoverage()` persists to `observability.runtime` in sprint-state.json |\n| 6 | **PASS** | Returns `skipped: true` with warning when backend unreachable, does NOT fail |\n| 7 | **FAIL** | Patch doesn't instruct verifiers to include observability evidence |\n\nThe core issue: the v0.23.1 npm package installed in the container does not include Story 5.2's changes (patch file update, verify prompt template with Step 3.5). The runtime infrastructure (gap parser, coverage persistence, graceful degradation) all work correctly — they were implemented in earlier epics.\n\n**Bonus finding**: `readPatchFile()` has a path resolution bug — it resolves `../../patches/` from `dist/` which goes outside the package directory. Patch files are never loaded from disk; the hardcoded fallback templates are always used.","stderr":"\nShell cwd was reset to /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
