{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01799af7sVfqtBp1fg78NfFY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 5.2: Verification Runtime Integration — Proof Document\n     2→\n     3→Verified: 2026-03-21\n     4→Package version: 0.23.1\n     5→Container: codeharness-verify\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## AC 1: Patch file includes Observability Evidence section [FAIL]\n    10→\n    11→The patch file `patches/verify/story-verification.md` exists in the installed package but does NOT contain the \"### Observability Evidence\" section required by this AC.\n    12→\n    13→```bash\n    14→docker exec codeharness-verify cat /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/verify/story-verification.md\n    15→```\n    16→\n    17→```output\n    18→## WHY\n    19→\n    20→Stories were marked \"done\" with no proof artifact, or with proofs that only\n    21→grepped source code instead of exercising the feature from the user's\n    22→perspective. This patch mandates black-box proof documents, docker exec evidence,\n    23→verification tags per AC, and test coverage targets — preventing regressions\n    24→from being hidden behind source-level assertions.\n    25→(FR33, FR36, NFR20)\n    26→\n    27→## Verification Requirements\n    28→\n    29→Every story must produce a **black-box proof** — evidence that the feature works from the user's perspective, NOT from reading source code.\n    30→\n    31→### Proof Standard\n    32→\n    33→- Proof document at `verification/<story-key>-proof.md`\n    34→- Each AC gets a `## AC N:` section with `docker exec` commands and captured output\n    35→- Evidence must come from running the installed CLI/tool, not from grepping source\n    36→- `[FAIL]` = AC failed with evidence showing what went wrong\n    37→- `[ESCALATE]` = AC genuinely cannot be automated (last resort — try everything first)\n    38→\n    39→### Verification Tags\n    40→\n    41→For each AC, append a tag indicating verification approach:\n    42→- `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` — default. Can be verified via CLI commands in a Docker container.\n    43→- `<!-- verification: integration-required -->` — requires external systems not available in the test environment (e.g., paid third-party APIs, physical hardware). This is rare — most things including workflows, agent sessions, and multi-step processes CAN be verified in Docker.\n    44→\n    45→**Do not over-tag.** Workflows, sprint planning, user sessions, slash commands, and agent behavior are all verifiable via `docker exec ... claude --print`. Only tag `integration-required` when there is genuinely no automated path.\n    46→\n    47→### Testing Requirements\n    48→\n    49→- Unit tests for all new/changed code\n    50→- Coverage target: 100% of new/changed lines\n    51→- No skipped tests without justification\n    52→```\n    53→\n    54→**Missing**: No \"### Observability Evidence\" section. No instruction to query observability backend after each `docker exec` command. No `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tagging instruction.\n    55→\n    56→Note: There is also a path resolution bug in `readPatchFile()` — it resolves to `join(__dirname, '..', '..', 'patches', ...)` which from `dist/` goes to `/usr/local/lib/node_modules/patches/` instead of `/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/`. The fallback template is always used, which also lacks the Observability Evidence section.\n    57→\n    58→```bash\n    59→docker exec codeharness-verify node --input-type=module -e \"\n    60→import { existsSync } from 'fs';\n    61→const distDir = '/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist';\n    62→import { join } from 'path';\n    63→const resolvedPath = join(distDir, '..', '..', 'patches', 'verify', 'story-verification.md');\n    64→console.log('readPatchFile resolves to:', resolvedPath);\n    65→console.log('Exists:', existsSync(resolvedPath));\n    66→const correctPath = join(distDir, '..', 'patches', 'verify', 'story-verification.md');\n    67→console.log('Correct path:', correctPath);\n    68→console.log('Correct exists:', existsSync(correctPath));\n    69→\"\n    70→```\n    71→\n    72→```output\n    73→readPatchFile resolves to: /usr/local/lib/node_modules/patches/verify/story-verification.md\n    74→Exists: false\n    75→Correct path: /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/verify/story-verification.md\n    76→Correct exists: true\n    77→```\n    78→\n    79→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n    80→\n    81→---\n    82→\n    83→## AC 2: verify-prompt.ts contains Step 3.5 observability check instructions [FAIL]\n    84→\n    85→\"Step 3.5\" does not exist anywhere in the installed v0.23.1 package. The bundle contains \"### Observability Check\" once, but it is in the `devEnforcementPatch()` fallback, not in a verify prompt template.\n    86→\n    87→```bash\n    88→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c \"grep -rc 'Step 3.5' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v ':0$' || echo 'NOT FOUND: Step 3.5 does not exist in any file'\"\n    89→```\n    90→\n    91→```output\n    92→NOT FOUND: Step 3.5 does not exist in any file\n    93→```\n    94→\n    95→```bash\n    96→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c \"grep -c 'Observability Check' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\"\n    97→```\n    98→\n    99→```output\n   100→1\n   101→```\n   102→\n   103→The single \"Observability Check\" match is in `devEnforcementPatch()`, not a verify prompt:\n   104→\n   105→```bash\n   106→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c \"grep -B 3 -A 3 'Observability Check' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\"\n   107→```\n   108→\n   109→```output\n   110→function devEnforcementPatch() {\n   111→  return readPatchFile(\"dev\", \"enforcement\") ?? `## Codeharness Enforcement\n   112→\n   113→### Observability Check\n   114→- [ ] Query VictoriaLogs after test runs to verify telemetry flows\n   115→\n   116→### Documentation Update\n   117→```\n   118→\n   119→No `verifyPromptTemplate()` function found. No VictoriaLogs query URL in a verify prompt context. The verify prompt template with \"Step 3.5\" is not present in v0.23.1.\n   120→\n   121→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n   122→\n   123→---\n   124→\n   125→## AC 3: parseObservabilityGaps returns correct values [PASS]\n   126→\n   127→Tested `parseObservabilityGaps` logic (extracted from compiled bundle) with a proof document containing 8 AC sections and 2 with `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tags.\n   128→\n   129→```bash\n   130→docker exec codeharness-verify node --input-type=module -e \"\n   131→const AC_HEADING_PATTERN = /^##\\s+AC\\s+(\\d+)/i;\n   132→const OBSERVABILITY_GAP_TAG = '[OBSERVABILITY GAP]';\n   133→\n   134→function parseObservabilityGaps(proofContent) {\n   135→  const lines = proofContent.split('\\n');\n   136→  const entries = [];\n   137→  let currentAcId = null;\n   138→  let currentSectionLines = [];\n   139→  const flushSection = () => {\n   140→    if (currentAcId !== null) {\n   141→      const sectionText = currentSectionLines.join('\\n');\n   142→      const hasGap = sectionText.includes(OBSERVABILITY_GAP_TAG);\n   143→      const gapNote = hasGap ? 'No log events detected' : void 0;\n   144→      entries.push({ acId: currentAcId, hasGap, gapNote });\n   145→    }\n   146→  };\n   147→  for (const line of lines) {\n   148→    const match = AC_HEADING_PATTERN.exec(line);\n   149→    if (match) { flushSection(); currentAcId = match[1]; currentSectionLines = [line]; }\n   150→    else if (currentAcId !== null) { currentSectionLines.push(line); }\n   151→  }\n   152→  flushSection();\n   153→  const totalACs = entries.length;\n   154→  const gapCount = entries.filter(e => e.hasGap).length;\n   155→  const coveredCount = totalACs - gapCount;\n   156→  return { entries, totalACs, gapCount, coveredCount };\n   157→}\n   158→\n   159→const proof = [\n   160→  '## AC 1: First', 'evidence', 'Log events: 3',\n   161→  '## AC 2: Second', 'evidence', '[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected',\n   162→  '## AC 3: Third', 'evidence', 'Log events: 5',\n   163→  '## AC 4: Fourth', 'evidence', 'Log events: 2',\n   164→  '## AC 5: Fifth', 'evidence', '[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected',\n   165→  '## AC 6: Sixth', 'evidence', 'Log events: 1',\n   166→  '## AC 7: Seventh', 'evidence', 'Log events: 4',\n   167→  '## AC 8: Eighth', 'evidence', 'Log events: 7',\n   168→].join('\\n');\n   169→\n   170→const result = parseObservabilityGaps(proof);\n   171→console.log(JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));\n   172→const coverage = Math.round(result.coveredCount / result.totalACs * 100);\n   173→console.log('Coverage:', coverage + '%');\n   174→console.log('PASS:', result.totalACs === 8 && result.gapCount === 2 && result.coveredCount === 6 && coverage === 75);\n   175→\"\n   176→```\n   177→\n   178→```output\n   179→{\n   180→  \"entries\": [\n   181→    { \"acId\": \"1\", \"hasGap\": false },\n   182→    { \"acId\": \"2\", \"hasGap\": true, \"gapNote\": \"No log events detected\" },\n   183→    { \"acId\": \"3\", \"hasGap\": false },\n   184→    { \"acId\": \"4\", \"hasGap\": false },\n   185→    { \"acId\": \"5\", \"hasGap\": true, \"gapNote\": \"No log events detected\" },\n   186→    { \"acId\": \"6\", \"hasGap\": false },\n   187→    { \"acId\": \"7\", \"hasGap\": false },\n   188→    { \"acId\": \"8\", \"hasGap\": false }\n   189→  ],\n   190→  \"totalACs\": 8,\n   191→  \"gapCount\": 2,\n   192→  \"coveredCount\": 6\n   193→}\n   194→Coverage: 75%\n   195→PASS: true\n   196→```\n   197→\n   198→The function correctly identifies 8 AC sections, 2 with gaps, 6 covered, and 75% runtime observability coverage.\n   199→\n   200→The function exists in the compiled bundle at the expected location:\n   201→\n   202→```bash\n   203→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c \"grep -c 'function parseObservabilityGaps' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\"\n   204→```\n   205→\n   206→```output\n   207→1\n   208→```\n   209→\n   210→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n   211→\n   212→---\n   213→\n   214→## AC 4: VerifyResult includes observabilityGapCount and runtimeCoveragePercent [PASS]\n   215→\n   216→The `verifyStory()` function in the compiled bundle reads proof content, calls `parseObservabilityGaps()`, and includes both fields in the result object.\n   217→\n   218→```bash\n   219→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c \"grep -o '.\\{0,60\\}observabilityGapCount.\\{0,60\\}' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\"\n   220→```\n   221→\n   222→```output\n   223→let observabilityGapCount = 0;\n   224→    observabilityGapCount = gapResult.gapCount;\n   225→    observabilityGapCount,\n   226→```\n   227→\n   228→```bash\n   229→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c \"grep -o '.\\{0,60\\}runtimeCoveragePercent.\\{0,60\\}' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\"\n   230→```\n   231→\n   232→```output\n   233→let runtimeCoveragePercent = 0;\n   234→    runtimeCoveragePercent = gapResult.totalACs === 0 ? 0 : gapResult.covere\n   235→    runtimeCoveragePercent,\n   236→```\n   237→\n   238→The code flow in `verifyStory()`:\n   239→1. Reads proof content from file\n   240→2. Calls `parseObservabilityGaps(proofContent)`\n   241→3. Sets `observabilityGapCount = gapResult.gapCount`\n   242→4. Computes `runtimeCoveragePercent = coveredCount / totalACs * 100`\n   243→5. Includes both in the result object alongside `success`, `totalACs`, `verifiedCount`, etc.\n   244→\n   245→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n   246→\n   247→---\n   248→\n   249→## AC 5: saveRuntimeCoverage updates sprint-state.json [PASS]\n   250→\n   251→Tested `saveRuntimeCoverage()` from the observability module. It correctly persists runtime coverage data under `observability.runtime` in sprint-state.json, separate from static coverage.\n   252→\n   253→```bash\n   254→docker exec codeharness-verify node --input-type=module -e \"\n   255→import { saveRuntimeCoverage } from '/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js';\n   256→import { mkdirSync, writeFileSync, readFileSync } from 'fs';\n   257→import { join } from 'path';\n   258→\n   259→const dir = '/tmp/test-save-runtime-ac5';\n   260→mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n   261→writeFileSync(join(dir, 'sprint-state.json'), JSON.stringify({\n   262→  observability: { static: { coveragePercent: 50 } }\n   263→}));\n   264→\n   265→await saveRuntimeCoverage(dir, { coveragePercent: 75, acsWithLogs: 6, totalACs: 8 });\n   266→\n   267→const state = JSON.parse(readFileSync(join(dir, 'sprint-state.json'), 'utf-8'));\n   268→console.log(JSON.stringify(state, null, 2));\n   269→\"\n   270→```\n   271→\n   272→```output\n   273→{\n   274→  \"observability\": {\n   275→    \"static\": {\n   276→      \"coveragePercent\": 50\n   277→    },\n   278→    \"runtime\": {\n   279→      \"coveragePercent\": 75,\n   280→      \"lastValidationTimestamp\": \"2026-03-21T06:48:38.948Z\",\n   281→      \"modulesWithTelemetry\": 6,\n   282→      \"totalModules\": 8,\n   283→      \"telemetryDetected\": true\n   284→    },\n   285→    \"targets\": {\n   286→      \"runtimeTarget\": 60\n   287→    }\n   288→  }\n   289→}\n   290→```\n   291→\n   292→Verified:\n   293→- `observability.runtime.coveragePercent` = 75\n   294→- `observability.runtime.lastValidationTimestamp` present (ISO 8601)\n   295→- `observability.static.coveragePercent` = 50 (preserved, separate from runtime)\n   296→- Static and runtime coverage stored as separate objects under `observability`\n   297→\n   298→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n   299→\n   300→---\n   301→\n   302→## AC 6: Graceful degradation when observability stack is down [PASS]\n   303→\n   304→Tested `checkBackendHealth()` and `validateRuntime()` with an unreachable endpoint. The system gracefully handles the failure without blocking verification.\n   305→\n   306→```bash\n   307→docker exec codeharness-verify node --input-type=module -e \"\n   308→import { checkBackendHealth } from '/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js';\n   309→const result = await checkBackendHealth({ endpoint: 'http://localhost:99999' });\n   310→console.log('checkBackendHealth result:', result);\n   311→\"\n   312→```\n   313→\n   314→```output\n   315→checkBackendHealth result: false\n   316→```\n   317→\n   318→```bash\n   319→docker exec codeharness-verify node --input-type=module -e \"\n   320→import { validateRuntime } from '/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js';\n   321→import { mkdirSync, writeFileSync } from 'fs';\n   322→const dir = '/tmp/test-graceful-ac6';\n   323→mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n   324→writeFileSync(dir + '/sprint-state.json', '{}');\n   325→mkdirSync(dir + '/src', { recursive: true });\n   326→writeFileSync(dir + '/src/index.ts', 'console.log(1)');\n   327→const result = await validateRuntime(dir, { queryEndpoint: 'http://localhost:99999' });\n   328→console.log(JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));\n   329→\"\n   330→```\n   331→\n   332→```output\n   333→{\n   334→  \"success\": true,\n   335→  \"data\": {\n   336→    \"entries\": [],\n   337→    \"totalModules\": 0,\n   338→    \"modulesWithTelemetry\": 0,\n   339→    \"coveragePercent\": 0,\n   340→    \"skipped\": true,\n   341→    \"skipReason\": \"runtime validation skipped -- observability stack not available\"\n   342→  }\n   343→}\n   344→```\n   345→\n   346→The implementation confirms:\n   347→- `checkBackendHealth()` returns `false` for unreachable endpoints\n   348→- `validateRuntime()` returns `success: true` (does NOT fail)\n   349→- Result includes `skipped: true` and `skipReason: \"runtime validation skipped -- observability stack not available\"`\n   350→- This matches the AC requirement