cted to:\n   394→- Query observability backend after each `docker exec` command\n   395→- Include `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tags when zero log events are detected\n   396→- Include log query results alongside functional output\n   397→\n   398→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n   399→\n   400→---\n   401→\n   402→## Summary\n   403→\n   404→| AC | Description | Result |\n   405→|----|-------------|--------|\n   406→| 1 | Patch file has Observability Evidence section | **FAIL** — section not present in v0.23.1 |\n   407→| 2 | verify-prompt.ts has Step 3.5 observability check | **FAIL** — Step 3.5 not present in v0.23.1 |\n   408→| 3 | parseObservabilityGaps returns correct values | **PASS** — {totalACs: 8, gapCount: 2, coveredCount: 6}, 75% |\n   409→| 4 | VerifyResult has observabilityGapCount and runtimeCoveragePercent | **PASS** — both fields populated in verifyStory() |\n   410→| 5 | saveRuntimeCoverage updates sprint-state.json | **PASS** — persists under observability.runtime |\n   411→| 6 | Graceful degradation when stack is down | **PASS** — returns skipped:true, does not fail |\n   412→| 7 | Proof includes functional and observability evidence | **FAIL** — patch lacks observability instructions |\n   413→\n   414→**Overall: FAIL** — 4 of 7 ACs pass. ACs 1, 2, and 7 fail because the v0.23.1 package does not include Story 5.2's patch updates or the \"Step 3.5\" verify prompt template content.\n   415→\n   416→### Additional Finding: Path Resolution Bug\n   417→\n   418→`readPatchFile()` uses `join(__dirname, '..', '..', 'patches', ...)` which from `dist/` resolves to `/usr/local/lib/node_modules/patches/` (outside the package). The actual patch files at `/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/` are never read. The fallback template strings are always used. This is a pre-existing bug unrelated to Story 5.2 but affects all patch loading.\n   419→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e4658086-9562-443f-b0a9-42e8d393ffab","uuid":"a1f7ff85-0c01-4b1f-8fda-40a5a90623a2","timestamp":"2026-03-21T06:53:24.606Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/codeharness-verify-5-2-verification-runtime-integration/verification/5-2-verification-runtime-integration-proof.md","content":"# Story 5.2: Verification Runtime Integration — Proof Document\n\nVerified: 2026-03-21\nPackage version: 0.23.1\nContainer: codeharness-verify\n\n---\n\n## AC 1: Patch file includes Observability Evidence section [FAIL]\n\nThe patch file `patches/verify/story-verification.md` exists in the installed package but does NOT contain the \"### Observability Evidence\" section required by this AC.\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify cat /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/verify/story-verification.md\n```\n\n```output\n## WHY\n\nStories were marked \"done\" with no proof artifact, or with proofs that only\ngrepped source code instead of exercising the feature from the user's\nperspective. This patch mandates black-box proof documents, docker exec evidence,\nverification tags per AC, and test coverage targets — preventing regressions\nfrom being hidden behind source-level assertions.\n(FR33, FR36, NFR20)\n\n## Verification Requirements\n\nEvery story must produce a **black-box proof** — evidence that the feature works from the user's perspective, NOT from reading source code.\n\n### Proof Standard\n\n- Proof document at `verification/<story-key>-proof.md`\n- Each AC gets a `## AC N:` section with `docker exec` commands and captured output\n- Evidence must come from running the installed CLI/tool, not from grepping source\n- `[FAIL]` = AC failed with evidence showing what went wrong\n- `[ESCALATE]` = AC genuinely cannot be automated (last resort — try everything first)\n\n### Verification Tags\n\nFor each AC, append a tag indicating verification approach:\n- `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` — default. Can be verified via CLI commands in a Docker container.\n- `<!-- verification: integration-required -->` — requires external systems not available in the test environment (e.g., paid third-party APIs, physical hardware). This is rare — most things including workflows, agent sessions, and multi-step processes CAN be verified in Docker.\n\n**Do not over-tag.** Workflows, sprint planning, user sessions, slash commands, and agent behavior are all verifiable via `docker exec ... claude --print`. Only tag `integration-required` when there is genuinely no automated path.\n\n### Testing Requirements\n\n- Unit tests for all new/changed code\n- Coverage target: 100% of new/changed lines\n- No skipped tests without justification\n```\n\n**Missing**: No \"### Observability Evidence\" section. No instruction to query observability backend after each `docker exec` command. No `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tagging instruction.\n\nNote: There is also a path resolution bug in `readPatchFile()` — it resolves to `join(__dirname, '..', '..', 'patches', ...)` which from `dist/` goes to `/usr/local/lib/node_modules/patches/` instead of `/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/`. The fallback template is always used, which also lacks the Observability Evidence section.\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify node --input-type=module -e \"\nimport { existsSync } from 'fs';\nconst distDir = '/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist';\nimport { join } from 'path';\nconst resolvedPath = join(distDir, '..', '..', 'patches', 'verify', 'story-verification.md');\nconsole.log('readPatchFile resolves to:', resolvedPath);\nconsole.log('Exists:', existsSync(resolvedPath));\nconst correctPath = join(distDir, '..', 'patches', 'verify', 'story-verification.md');\nconsole.log('Correct path:', correctPath);\nconsole.log('Correct exists:', existsSync(correctPath));\n\"\n```\n\n```output\nreadPatchFile resolves to: /usr/local/lib/node_modules/patches/verify/story-verification.md\nExists: false\nCorrect path: /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/verify/story-verification.md\nCorrect exists: true\n```\n\n[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n\n---\n\n## AC 2: verify-prompt.ts contains Step 3.5 observability check instructions [FAIL]\n\n\"Step 3.5\" does not exist anywhere in the installed v0.23.1 package. The bundle contains \"### Observability Check\" once, but it is in the `devEnforcementPatch()` fallback, not in a verify prompt template.\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c \"grep -rc 'Step 3.5' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v ':0$' || echo 'NOT FOUND: Step 3.5 does not exist in any file'\"\n```\n\n```output\nNOT FOUND: Step 3.5 does not exist in any file\n```\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c \"grep -c 'Observability Check' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\"\n```\n\n```output\n1\n```\n\nThe single \"Observability Check\" match is in `devEnforcementPatch()`, not a verify prompt:\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c \"grep -B 3 -A 3 'Observability Check' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\"\n```\n\n```output\nfunction devEnforcementPatch() {\n  return readPatchFile(\"dev\", \"enforcement\") ?? `## Codeharness Enforcement\n\n### Observability Check\n- [ ] Query VictoriaLogs after test runs to verify telemetry flows\n\n### Documentation Update\n```\n\nNo `verifyPromptTemplate()` function found. No VictoriaLogs query URL in a verify prompt context. The verify prompt template with \"Step 3.5\" is not present in v0.23.1.\n\n[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n\n---\n\n## AC 3: parseObservabilityGaps returns correct values [PASS]\n\nTested `parseObservabilityGaps` logic (extracted from compiled bundle) with a proof document containing 8 AC sections and 2 with `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tags.\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify node --input-type=module -e \"\nconst AC_HEADING_PATTERN = /^##\\s+AC\\s+(\\d+)/i;\nconst OBSERVABILITY_GAP_TAG = '[OBSERVABILITY GAP]';\n\nfunction parseObservabilityGaps(proofContent) {\n  const lines = proofContent.split('\\n');\n  const entries = [];\n  let currentAcId = null;\n  let currentSectionLines = [];\n  const flushSection = () => {\n    if (currentAcId !== null) {\n      const sectionText = currentSectionLines.join('\\n');\n      const hasGap = sectionText.includes(OBSERVABILITY_GAP_TAG);\n      const gapNote = hasGap ? 'No log events detected' : void 0;\n      entries.push({ acId: currentAcId, hasGap, gapNote });\n    }\n  };\n  for (const line of lines) {\n    const match = AC_HEADING_PATTERN.exec(line);\n    if (match) { flushSection(); currentAcId = match[1]; currentSectionLines = [line]; }\n    else if (currentAcId !== null) { currentSectionLines.push(line); }\n  }\n  flushSection();\n  const totalACs = entries.length;\n  const gapCount = entries.filter(e => e.hasGap).length;\n  const coveredCount = totalACs - gapCount;\n  return { entries, totalACs, gapCount, coveredCount };\n}\n\nconst proof = [\n  '## AC 1: First', 'evidence', 'Log events: 3',\n  '## AC 2: Second', 'evidence', '[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected',\n  '## AC 3: Third', 'evidence', 'Log events: 5',\n  '## AC 4: Fourth', 'evidence', 'Log events: 2',\n  '## AC 5: Fifth', 'evidence', '[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected',\n  '## AC 6: Sixth', 'evidence', 'Log events: 1',\n  '## AC 7: Seventh', 'evidence', 'Log events: 4',\n  '## AC 8: Eighth', 'evidence', 'Log events: 7',\n].join('\\n');\n\nconst result = parseObservabilityGaps(proof);\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));\nconst coverage = Math.round(result.coveredCount / result.totalACs * 100);\nconsole.log('Coverage:', coverage + '%');\nconsole.log('PASS:', result.totalACs === 8 && result.gapCount === 2 && result.coveredCount === 6 && coverage === 75);\n\"\n```\n\n```output\n{\n  \"entries\": [\n    { \"acId\": \"1\", \"hasGap\": false },\n    { \"acId\": \"2\", \"hasGap\": true, \"gapNote\": \"No log events detected\" },\n    { \"acId\": \"3\", \"hasGap\": false },\n    { \"acId\": \"4\", \"hasGap\": false },\n    { \"acId\": \"5\", \"hasGap\": true, \"gapNote\": \"No log events detected\" },\n    { \"acId\": \"6\", \"hasGap\": false },\n    { \"acId\": \"7\", \"hasGap\": false },\n    { \"acId\": \"8\", \"hasGap\": false }\n  ],\n  \"totalACs\": 8,\n  \"gapCount\": 2,\n  \"coveredCount\": 6\n}\nCoverage: 75%\nPASS: true\n```\n\nThe function correctly identifies 8 AC sections, 2 with gaps, 6 covered, and 75% runtime observability coverage.\n\nThe function exists in the compiled bundle at the expected location:\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c \"grep -c 'function parseObservabilityGaps' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\"\n```\n\n```output\n1\n```\n\n[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n\n---\n\n## AC 4: VerifyResult includes observabilityGapCount and runtimeCoveragePercent [PASS]\n\nThe `verifyStory()` function in the compiled bundle reads proof content, calls `parseObservabilityGaps()`, and includes both fields in the result object.\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c \"grep -o '.\\{0,60\\}observabilityGapCount.\\{0,60\\}' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\"\n```\n\n```output\nlet observabilityGapCount = 0;\n    observabilityGapCount = gapResult.gapCount;\n    observabilityGapCount,\n```\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c \"grep -o '.\\{0,60\\}runtimeCoveragePercent.\\{0,60\\}' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\"\n```\n\n```output\nlet runtimeCoveragePercent = 0;\n    runtimeCoveragePercent = gapResult.totalACs === 0 ? 0 : gapResult.covere\n    runtimeCoveragePercent,\n```\n\nThe code flow in `verifyStory()`:\n1. Reads proof content from file\n2. Calls `parseObservabilityGaps(proofContent)`\n3. Sets `observabilityGapCount = gapResult.gapCount`\n4. Computes `runtimeCoveragePercent = coveredCount / totalACs * 100`\n5. Includes both in the result object alongside `success`, `totalACs`, `verifiedCount`, etc.\n\n[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n\n---\n\n## AC 5: saveRuntimeCoverage updates sprint-state.json [PASS]\n\nTested `saveRuntimeCoverage()` from the observability module. It correctly persists runtime coverage data under `observability.runtime` in sprint-state.json, separate from static coverage.\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify node --input-type=module -e \"\nimport { saveRuntimeCoverage } from '/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js';\nimport { mkdirSync, writeFileSync, readFileSync } from 'fs';\nimport { join } from 'path';\n\nconst dir = '/tmp/test-save-runtime-ac5';\nmkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\nwriteFileSync(join(dir, 'sprint-state.json'), JSON.stringify({\n  observability: { static: { coveragePercent: 50 } }\n}));\n\nawait saveRuntimeCoverage(dir, { coveragePercent: 75, acsWithLogs: 6, totalACs: 8 });\n\nconst state = JSON.parse(readFileSync(join(dir, 'sprint-state.json'), 'utf-8'));\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify(state, null, 2));\n\"\n```\n\n```output\n{\n  \"observability\": {\n    \"static\": {\n      \"coveragePercent\": 50\n    },\n    \"runtime\": {\n      \"coveragePercent\": 75,\n      \"lastValidationTimestamp\": \"2026-03-21T06:48:38.948Z\",\n      \"modulesWithTelemetry\": 6,\n      \"totalModules\": 8,\n      \"telemetryDetected\": true\n    },\n    \"targets\": {\n      \"runtimeTarget\": 60\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nVerified:\n- `observability.runtime.coveragePercent` = 75\n- `observability.runtime.lastValidationTimestamp` present (ISO 8601)\n- `observability.static.coveragePercent` = 50 (preserved, separate from runtime)\n- Static and runtime coverage stored as separate objects under `observability`\n\n[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n\n---\n\n## AC 6: Graceful degradation when observability stack is down [PASS]\n\nTested `checkBackendHealth()` and `validateRuntime()` with an unreachable endpoint. The system gracefully handles the failure without blocking verification.\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify node --input-type=module -e \"\nimport { checkBackendHealth } from '/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js';\nconst result = await checkBackendHealth({ endpoint: 'http://localhost:99999' });\nconsole.log('checkBackendHealth result:', result);\n\"\n```\n\n```output\ncheckBackendHealth result: false\n```\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify node --input-type=module -e \"\nimport { validateRuntime } from '/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js';\nimport { mkdirSync, writeFileSync } from 'fs';\nconst dir = '/tmp/test-graceful-ac6';\nmkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\nwriteFileSync(dir + '/sprint-state.json', '{}');\nmkdirSync(dir + '/src', { recursive: true });\nwriteFileSync(dir + '/src/index.ts', 'console.log(1)');\nconst result = await validateRuntime(dir, { queryEndpoint: 'http://localhost:99999' });\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));\n\"\n```\n\n```output\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"entries\": [],\n    \"totalModules\": 0,\n    \"modulesWithTelemetry\": 0,\n    \"coveragePercent\": 0,\n    \"skipped\": true,\n    \"skipReason\": \"runtime validation skipped -- observability stack not available\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe implementation confirms:\n- `checkBackendHealth()` returns `false` for unreachable endpoints\n- `validateRuntime()` returns `success: true` (does NOT fail)\n- Result includes `skipped: true` and `skipReason: \"runtime validation skipped -- observability stack not available\"`\n- This matches the AC requirement: \"reports 'observability check skipped — backend not reachable' as a warning and does NOT fail the verification\"\n\nSource code confirms the pattern:\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c \"grep -A 10 'if (!healthy)' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js\"\n```\n\n```output\n  if (!healthy) {\n    const modules2 = discoverModules(projectDir);\n    const entries2 = modules2.map((m) => ({\n      moduleName: m,\n      telemetryDetected: false,\n      eventCount: 0\n    }));\n    return ok({\n      entries: entries2,\n      totalModules: modules2.length,\n      modulesWithTelemetry: 0,\n      coveragePercent: 0,\n      skipped: true,\n      skipReason: \"runtime validation skipped -- observability stack not available\"\n```\n\n[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n\n---\n\n## AC 7: Proof document includes both functional and observability evidence [FAIL]\n\nThis AC requires that the verification patch instructs the verifier to include both functional evidence (`docker exec` output) and observability evidence (log query results or `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tags) for each AC.\n\nThe patch file does NOT contain observability evidence instructions (same root cause as AC 1):\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c \"grep -c 'observability\\|OBSERVABILITY\\|log query\\|log events' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/verify/story-verification.md\"\n```\n\n```output\n0\n```\n\nThe patch instructs functional verification (`docker exec` commands, proof documents) but has no observability evidence instructions. Without the \"### Observability Evidence\" section, verifiers are not instructed to:\n- Query observability backend after each `docker exec` command\n- Include `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tags when zero log events are detected\n- Include log query results alongside functional output\n\n[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Description | Result |\n|----|-------------|--------|\n| 1 | Patch file has Observability Evidence section | **FAIL** — section not present in v0.23.1 |\n| 2 | verify-prompt.ts has Step 3.5 observability check | **FAIL** — Step 3.5 not present in v0.23.1 |\n| 3 | parseObservabilityGaps returns correct values | **PASS** — {totalACs: 8, gapCount: 2, coveredCount: 6}, 75% |\n| 4 | VerifyResult has observabilityGapCount and runtimeCoveragePercent | **PASS** — both fields populated in verifyStory() |\n| 5 | saveRuntimeCoverage updates sprint-state.json | **PASS** — persists under observability.runtime |\n| 6 | Graceful degradation when stack is down | **PASS** — returns skipped:true, does not fail |\n| 7 | Proof includes functional and observability evidence | **FAIL** — patch lacks observability instructions |\n\n**Overall: FAIL** — 4 of 7 ACs pass. ACs 1, 2, and 7 fail because the v0.23.1 package does not include Story 5.2's patch updates or the \"Step 3.5\" verify prompt template content.\n\n### Additional Finding: Path Resolution Bug\n\n`readPatchFile()` uses `join(__dirname, '..', '..', 'patches', ...)` which from `dist/` resolves to `/usr/local/lib/node_modules/patches/` (outside the package). The actual patch files at `/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/` are never read. The fallback template strings are always used. This is a pre-existing bug unrelated to Story 5.2 but affects all patch loading.\n","numLines":419,"startLine":1,"totalLines":419}}}
