I need a way to actually exercise the function from within the container environment.\n\nThe cleanest solution is to make `verifyPromptTemplate` available in the compiled output—either as a re-export from the observability module or as a separate entry point. But I'm running low on time, maybe 13 minutes left, and re-running the full verifier will take several minutes. I could try compiling the TypeScript directly in the container with tsx if it's available, or I could manually verify the failing acceptance criteria and update the proof document since the infrastructure issue is clear. The process does require black-box verification in Docker though, so I need to find the fastest valid approach.\n\nThe patches are now in the container which fixes two of the failing criteria, and for the third one I can either install tsx to compile the template or copy over the compiled file. Rather than re-running the entire verifier, I could manually update the proof document with evidence from the updated container since the infrastructure fix is already in place. But the verification process requires actually running the verifier session. Let me focus on a targeted re-verification that only checks the three failing criteria instead of the whole suite.\n\nActually, I'll just re-run the full verifier with the updated container—it should be quick since most checks are straightforward, so I'll delete the old proof and run it fresh.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":402,"cache_read_input_tokens":65317,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":402},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e4658086-9562-443f-b0a9-42e8d393ffab","uuid":"5c206731-b2cc-431c-8548-83771a70baf4"}
