{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01SVUJovucgzYXYkfN22TBqk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015dxiin3DLhAJrmMFQdmvsC","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/codeharness-verify-5-2-verification-runtime-integration/verify-prompt-2.txt","content":"You are a black-box verifier. Your job is to verify that a software feature works correctly. You have NO access to source code, but the built artifacts are installed in a Docker container.\n\n## Context\n\nThe container `codeharness-verify` has been updated with the latest build artifacts:\n- Updated patches at `/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/`\n- Updated dist at `/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/`\n- `tsx` is installed globally for running TypeScript files\n- The verify-prompt.ts template is at `/tmp/verify-templates/verify-prompt.ts`\n\nThe `verifyPromptTemplate()` function was tree-shaken from the dist bundle because it's only used by the skill system, not the CLI. To test it, use tsx to import and call it from `/tmp/verify-templates/verify-prompt.ts`.\n\n## Step 1: Read Story\n\nRead `story.md` in this workspace. It has 7 acceptance criteria.\n\n## Step 2: Verify Each AC\n\nRun commands via `docker exec codeharness-verify ...` and capture evidence.\n\n### AC 1: Patch file has \"### Observability Evidence\" section\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify cat /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/verify/story-verification.md\n```\nCheck that it contains \"### Observability Evidence\", instruction to query observability backend after each docker exec, and [OBSERVABILITY GAP] tagging instruction.\n\n### AC 2: verifyPromptTemplate() includes Step 3.5\nUse tsx to import and call the function:\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify tsx -e \"\nimport { verifyPromptTemplate } from '/tmp/verify-templates/verify-prompt.ts';\nconst result = verifyPromptTemplate({ storyKey: 'test', storyContent: 'test content' });\nconsole.log('Has Step 3.5:', result.includes('Step 3.5'));\nconsole.log('Has VictoriaLogs URL:', result.includes('localhost:9428'));\nconsole.log('Has OBSERVABILITY GAP:', result.includes('[OBSERVABILITY GAP]'));\nconsole.log('Has Observability Check:', result.includes('Observability Check After Each Command'));\n\"\n```\n\n### AC 3: parseObservabilityGaps returns correct values\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify node --input-type=module -e \"\nimport { parseObservabilityGaps } from '/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js';\nconst proof = [\n  '## AC 1: First', 'evidence', 'Log events: 3',\n  '## AC 2: Second', 'evidence', '[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected',\n  '## AC 3: Third', 'evidence', 'Log events: 5',\n  '## AC 4: Fourth', 'evidence', 'Log events: 2',\n  '## AC 5: Fifth', 'evidence', '[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected',\n  '## AC 6: Sixth', 'evidence', 'Log events: 1',\n  '## AC 7: Seventh', 'evidence', 'Log events: 4',\n  '## AC 8: Eighth', 'evidence', 'Log events: 7',\n].join('\\n');\nconst result = parseObservabilityGaps(proof);\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));\nconst pct = Math.round(result.coveredCount / result.totalACs * 100);\nconsole.log('Coverage:', pct + '%');\nconsole.log('PASS:', result.totalACs === 8 && result.gapCount === 2 && result.coveredCount === 6 && pct === 75);\n\"\n```\n\n### AC 4: VerifyResult has observabilityGapCount and runtimeCoveragePercent\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c \"grep -o '.\\{0,60\\}observabilityGapCount.\\{0,60\\}' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\"\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c \"grep -o '.\\{0,60\\}runtimeCoveragePercent.\\{0,60\\}' /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\"\n```\n\n### AC 5: saveRuntimeCoverage updates sprint-state.json under observability.runtime\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify node --input-type=module -e \"\nimport { saveRuntimeCoverage } from '/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js';\nimport { mkdirSync, writeFileSync, readFileSync } from 'fs';\nconst dir = '/tmp/test-ac5';\nmkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\nwriteFileSync(dir + '/sprint-state.json', JSON.stringify({observability: {static: {coveragePercent: 50}}}));\nawait saveRuntimeCoverage(dir, { coveragePercent: 75, acsWithLogs: 6, totalACs: 8 });\nconst state = JSON.parse(readFileSync(dir + '/sprint-state.json', 'utf-8'));\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify(state, null, 2));\nconsole.log('PASS:', state.observability.runtime.coveragePercent === 75 && state.observability.static.coveragePercent === 50);\n\"\n```\n\n### AC 6: Graceful degradation when stack is down\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify node --input-type=module -e \"\nimport { checkBackendHealth, validateRuntime } from '/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/modules/observability/index.js';\nimport { mkdirSync, writeFileSync } from 'fs';\nconst healthy = await checkBackendHealth({ endpoint: 'http://localhost:99999' });\nconsole.log('checkBackendHealth:', healthy);\nconst dir = '/tmp/test-ac6';\nmkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\nwriteFileSync(dir + '/sprint-state.json', '{}');\nmkdirSync(dir + '/src', { recursive: true });\nwriteFileSync(dir + '/src/index.ts', 'console.log(1)');\nconst result = await validateRuntime(dir, { queryEndpoint: 'http://localhost:99999' });\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));\nconsole.log('PASS:', result.success === true && result.data.skipped === true);\n\"\n```\n\n### AC 7: Patch instructs verifier to include both functional and observability evidence\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify cat /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/verify/story-verification.md\n```\nVerify the patch contains instructions for:\n1. Functional evidence (docker exec output) — should already be there\n2. Observability evidence (log query results or [OBSERVABILITY GAP] tags) — from the new Observability Evidence section\n\n## Step 3: Observability Check\n\nAfter EACH docker exec, query:\n```bash\ncurl 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&start=-30s&limit=100'\n```\nIf zero events, add `[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction` to that AC section.\n\n## Step 4: Write Proof Document\n\nWrite to: `verification/5-2-verification-runtime-integration-proof.md`\n\nFormat for each AC:\n```text\n## AC N: <description>\n\n```bash\n<command>\n```\n\n```output\n<actual output>\n```\n\nVerdict: [PASS] or [FAIL] or [ESCALATE]\n```\n\n**IMPORTANT: Only use `bash` and `output` as code fence languages.** Never use bare ``` fences without a language tag.\n\n## Critical Rules\n\n1. ALL commands MUST use `docker exec codeharness-verify ...`\n2. No source code access\n3. Report REAL failures — do NOT fabricate evidence\n4. Every AC needs functional evidence\n5. [ESCALATE] only for genuinely impossible automation (physical hardware, paid services)\n6. Infrastructure problems are [FAIL], not [ESCALATE]\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":258,"cache_read_input_tokens":67089,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":258},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e4658086-9562-443f-b0a9-42e8d393ffab","uuid":"856cafc2-d3a1-4630-977d-bccc0badd17d"}
